                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=campasau",
                        "name": "campasau",
                        "displayName": "-.-",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Line 111 in this fix is unnessesary.\n\n{noformat}\n$name = ucwords($name);\n{noformat}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=campasau",
                        "name": "campasau",
                        "displayName": "-.-",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-11T03:58:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-11T03:58:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30847",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Um, yes, that line *is* necessary -- that's precisely the functionality implemented in the dispatcher's getModuleName() method (via _formatName()). It allows the ability to translate foo-bar to FooBar -- without ucwords(), it would be simply Foobar -- which is incorrect.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-11T05:57:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-11T05:57:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30851",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jpadron",
                        "name": "jpadron",
                        "displayName": "Jorge Padron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, the function ucwords() is necessary, but it's used twice: lines 111-112",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jpadron",
